    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-19T04:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-19T04:34:00-05:00" n="206"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <head>206. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d206fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 6, Folder 2. Secret. Repeated to the Director of Central
                        Intelligence and to <gloss target="#t_SHERWOOD1">SHERWOOD</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-19T09:34:00+00:00">June 19, 1954,
                        0934Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>4062. Ref: [<hi rend="italic">telegram indicator not declassified</hi>] 650.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d206fn2">Not printed. (Ibid., Box 13, Folder 7)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>No authority to bomb at present, also army may swing our side soon.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Avoid attack and bypass <gloss target="#t_HANK1">Hank</gloss> while having
                        air show by fighters for benefit garrison.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>If fear or dislike regime does not bring army over in day more forceful
                        air support will have to be provided.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Try one day guerrilla tactics with air show. Meanwhile we are requesting
                        authority for real air support to be ready if necessary. In meantime can
                        assure you have realistic hope that army may turn against regime. Cannot
                        afford risk this opportunity by bomb or other attack until make effort find
                        out.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_SHERWOOD1">SHERWOOD</gloss>: Order supply bombs moved to
                        SOMERSET to be ready by dawn 20 June.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
